Node.Notes: Despite presence of "and" (often seen as emphatic, "now/please"), the translation should probably still be "For the sake of your name, O LORD, forgive my iniquity for it is great."
It is "because" of how great the inquity is that the appeal for forgiveness is for the sake of Yahweh's name. So, "for/because" more likely than concessive "though."
Aone, without anyone to help/protect him.
Probably two qualities of the psalmist's character.
